    {
        "content": "<p>VolodymyrBg opened <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/10360\">PR #10360</a> from <code>VolodymyrBg:BG</code> to <code>bytecodealliance:main</code>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Previously, the CLI interface would only accept base-10 (decimal) integers when <br>\npassing arguments to WebAssembly functions. This change adds support for <br>\nhexadecimal notation with the '0x' prefix.</p>\n<p>Now users can pass hexadecimal values directly to functions that expect integer<br>\narguments, making it more convenient to work with bit patterns, addresses, and<br>\nother values commonly represented in hexadecimal format.</p>\n<p>Fixes the TODO comment in the <a href=\"http://run.rs\">run.rs</a> file that requested this feature.</p>\n</blockquote>",
